# Tools

## ShinyApps

```{r eval=FALSE, echo=FALSE}
### RNAseq data visualization

A very simple shiny app to visualize RNAseq data from the [Snakemake RNAseq pipeline](https://github.com/dfernandezperez/RNAseq-Snakemake/tree/development) used in the Pasini's Lab.

The code is available [here](https://github.com/amitjavilaventura/ShinyApps/tree/main/shiny_rnaseq).

### ChIPseq data visualization

A very simple shiny app to visualize the ChIPseq data from the [Snakemake ChIPseq pipeline](https://github.com/dfernandezperez/ChIPseq-snakemake/tree/development) used in the Pasini's lab.

The code is available [here](https://github.com/amitjavilaventura/ShinyApps/tree/main/shiny_chipseq).
```

### DNAme 

Simple ShinyApp for teaching/learning purposes, that converts a name to nucleotide (DNA or mRNA) sequence. 

Not all names can be converted, since *DNAme* takes each letter as an aminoacid, and not all letters are one-letter code for aminoacids.

The app is avialable [here](https://biobit.netlify.app/dname.html) and the source code is available [here](https://github.com/amitjavilaventura/DNAme).

```{r biobit, echo=FALSE, fig.cap="DNAme logo.", layout="l-body"}
knitr::include_graphics("assets/DNAme_logo.png")
```

